  "body": "# Feature request: Add Reverse Range Filter for logs And use `blockCount` & `toBlock` as Pagination parameters\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature exist?\r\n1. Users care more about the latest relevant logs data than the historical logs' data. If the user only wants to query the latest / recent 20 blocks of logs matching the `FilterCriteria`, the computation of older blocks would be a huge waste.\r\n2. The results of the `eth_getLogs` API return are hard to get pagination when the logs' length is big. Maybe adding pagination parameters of `blockCount` & `toBlock` can help to make a pagination.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\nYes.",
